Allow for a float as time specification as README.md suggests (#95)

Allow for a float as time specification as README.md suggests

First I thought that it might be better to just fix the README.md which
gives example.

     nosetests --with-timer --timer-warning 5.0 --timer-fail error

but then decided that it would be better to fix the code to allow for such floating
number specification

commit.message:
Update .travis.yml to use PyPI token.  (#94)

* Updated password in PyPi which will break tag on release. I migrated to PyPI tokens instead and updated the .travis.yml as a result

* Remove secure: as that's not needed since we are using travis set env because encrypting the PyPI token causes an error message 'data too large - consider using travis encrypt-file or travis env set'

commit.message: Change badges from png to svg
Use Python 3.8 for deploy to PyPi
Allow lines up-to 120 symbols by flake8
Use assertEqual intead of deprecated assertEquals

Add package __version__

The following should work:

```
>>> import nosetimer
>>> nosetimer.__version__
'0.7.4'
```
Do not install unwanted packages for pep8 env
